# 3. Alternate method (skip if you did above)
If you using X11 instead of Wayland here is an alternative fix.
So would apply to any X11 users (i3,XFCE,Qtile,dwm,ect) or Linux Mint which defualt is X11

![Alt text](images/czn/image3.webp)
Go to the Settigns Page and Press WINECFG
(this is to open wine configuration)
Now you can press install
![Alt text](images/czn/image4.webp )
Press the Graphics Tab
Now you can press install
![Alt text](images/czn/image5.webp )
Press emulate virtual desktop.
(Can change the default size if you want).
Press Apply then OK

# 4. 
Launch the game like from Heroic or whatever app you are using and it the bug should be gone.

Can remove the fix you applied by either unticking the box  or disbaling virtual desktop by unticking and doing the same steps
